parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and loss of power can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the "Service Stabilitrak" and "Service Engine" lights come on
the vehicle jerks or hesitates
and the speedometer and tachometer gauges malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system malfunctions can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system malfunctions
causing the dashboard lights to flash
the engine to stall
and the vehicle to lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch and transmission issues can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
and the transmission slips or fails to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defroster and heating issues can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The defroster fails to defrost the windshield
the heater control knob fails
and the entire instrument panel illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fire hazards can cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
especially under the hood
and emits dark smoke and flames.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to lose steering ability, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the power steering pump makes a loud noise
the vehicle loses power steering fluid
the steering wheel locks or becomes stuck
the vehicle shakes or vibrates while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine stops running while driving
the vehicle loses power
the steering and brakes become inoperable
the vehicle shakes or vibrates while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The steering wheel pull can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel feels difficult to turn
the vehicle drifts or wanders while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine trouble light illuminates
the engine powers down
the vehicle stalls
the front end shakes
and the engine makes a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Reduced Engine Power/Throttle Control Assembly Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle control assembly can cause the engine to lose power, leading to a loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The reduced engine power warning indicator illuminates
the vehicle loses forward momentum
the braking and power steering ability seize
and the vehicle stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage and potentially a loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The coolant system light comes on
the service oil light comes on
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle overheats
and a noise is heard under the car while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine warning indicator illuminates
the vehicle stalls
and rodents chew through the oxygen 2 sensor wire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle's electrical system can cause a fire, which can lead to injuries and property damage.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle catches on fire
and the fire spreads to the surrounding area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil level sensor can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The oil level sensor is inoperable
and the vehicle stalls.
